ely show an even steeper growth rate. The International Energy Agency has long projected geothermal could be a serious solution to climate change. In a 2011 roadmap document, IEA suggested geothermal could reach some 3.5% of global electricity generation annually by 2050, avoiding almost 800 megatonnes of carbon dioxide emissions per year. This article contains reporting from the Associated Press. Geothermal News Renewables data centers Google NV Energy ### Steam generator condenser performance monitoring (Part 4) This installment examines how microbiological fouling, corrosion and condenser tube leaks can trigger cooling water  ...    11 min read\n\nNews O&M\n\n### Simplifying Measurement in Renewable Natural Gas (RNG) Production  ...    ArcLight acquires stake in 5.4 GW of power projects, Arevon closes on $920M in financing, Aypa Power secures funding  ...    ### Peak Energy and RWE deploying sodium-ion battery in Wisconsin  ...    5 min read\n\nBatteries Energy Storage News ### FERC streamlines NEPA reviews for low-impact hydro actions The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission voted to streamline NEPA reviews for water power actions with minimal  ...    2 min read\n\nHydropower News Renewables"
